ndbreaking book illuminates the changing definitions of family and suggests a model for law reform that would enable the legal recognition of alternative forms of parentage. The first empirical study in Canada to address the legal dimensions of planned lesbian families, this book makes an important contribution to family law, queer studies, and law reform literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLaw reformxCanada. 0aLaw reformzCanada. 0aLesbian couples as parentsxLegal status, laws, etcxCanada. 0aLesbian couples as parentsxLegal status, laws, etczCanada. 0aLesbian mothersxFamily relationshipsxCanada. 0aLesbian mothersxFamily relationshipszCanada. 0aLesbian mothersxInterviewsxCanada. 0aLesbian mothersxLegal status, laws, etcxCanada. 0aLesbian mothersxLegal status, laws, etczCanada. 0aLesbian motherszCanadavInterviews. 0aMères lesbiennesxDroitxCanada. 0aMères lesbiennesxEntretiensxCanada. 0aParent and child (Law)xCanada. 0aParent and child (Law)zCanada. 0aParents et enfants (Droit)xCanada. 0aParents homosexuelsxDroitxCanada. 7aLAW / Family Law / Children.2bisacsh1 aBumsted, J.M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481965740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774819657423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774819657/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2